<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST964>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:disaster@tempusmud.com"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Moradinson<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Friday, May 4, 2001 - 10:33 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> It be Faire Season!  Throughout th&#39; lands o Earth this be a common time o&#39; year fer crazy folk ta doff their business clothes and git dressed up like they was lords, ladies, musketeers, strumpets, pirates, gypisies, highlanders, etc... an go to ren faires! <BR> <BR>Watchin alla th&#39; hullabaloo has fostered in me an idea.  I plan to hold an in-game Dwarven Faire Event.  This will be my most ambitious event undertaking to date as your chief. <BR> <BR>I plan to hold the faire on a Saturday.  The faire will consist of a series of contests/games and raffles with dwarven themes. <BR> <BR>I&#39;ll start accepting donations for the platinum and item raffles anytime.  Meanwhile, as the raffle pot grows, I&#39;ll be coming up with game and raffle rules, and arranging for this event to be advertised on several high profile websites. <BR> <BR>What I&#39;ll need from ye kin is: <BR> <BR>-Volunteers to run individual &#34;booths&#34; - These are to be small games &#40;trivia, races, etc&#41;. The Axepeak running the booth will group with up to 5 players at a time.  By using the group, the dwarf running that &#34;booth&#34; will be able to have a channel just for his/her game.  In order to minimize logistics of waiting lists etc, I&#39;ll suggest that the booth-runner just shout something like:  <BR>&#124;FIRST FIVE PEOPLE TO POKE ME MAY PLAY IN THE DWARVEN FAIRE TRIVIA BOOTH!  PRIZE IS 10 PLATINUM!&#124; <BR> <BR>-donations of items for the raffles.  I&#39;ll break the items donated out into useful packages, and raffle them out as preludes to the finale platinum raffle.  The platinum pot will consist of whatever seed money is donated, along with the total of the sold tickets.  I plan to charge 50 platinum per ticket, and limit each character to 5 tickets maximum. <BR> <BR>-Ideas!  If this is to be more than a day of watching the text channels spam across your screens, we&#39;ll need some interesting and original ideas for games and events.   <BR> <BR>-Storm Moradinson <BR>Clan Axepeak Rorn Gor <BR>Old Mithrilbones <!-/Text-!> <P> 
