<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST973>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:worried70@hotmail.com"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Badaph<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Monday, May 7, 2001 - 02:23 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Some other idears: <BR> <BR>Dwarven dueling in the arena in Kaladim. We can just go bare knuckle &#40;although probably nay be able ta hit yer opponent if everyone wears their best armor&#41; or use weapons to speed things up a bit. Each oppenent has ta down 5 or so dwarven ales before the round starts of course.  <BR> <BR>Something else i always thought might be fun but would take alot of coordination and around 32 dwarves. A dwarven chess match. Everyone makes a 1st level dwarf of various types. Pawns=1st level warriors with no armor. Bishops= 1st level clerics in banded. Rooks= 1st level rogues with banded armor &#40;visible only&#41;, Knights=first level paladins in banded with a shield. The King and Queen can be Paladins or Warriors and would wear bronze or fine steel, maybe just a BP and the rest banded and weild a fine steel weapon.  <BR> <BR>Also each team would have a leader that directs the moves.   <BR> <BR>Of course the match would take place on the chess board in BB. This presents 2 problems however. First off, some of the squares are occupied by stone pieces. So we would have to work around them somehow. Secondly undead minions spawn there. These would easily kill any 1st level people there. So we would have to deal with them somehow. I suspect we would have to have someone close of higher level to kill them quickly, maybe remain sitting at one their spawn point to get that first agro. Course the ones actually on the chessboard would mean someone would have to sit in the way.  This would also prevent your normal adventurers that frequent their from killing them.  <BR> <BR>The &#34;pieces&#34; are moved by the direction commanded by that teams leader. When one dwarf enters the square of another dwarf they /duel and the winner gets the square. He does not get a heal however. What this does is make the other team&#39;s captain make a move quickly. If an enemy unit is hurt you want to attack it fast since 1st level characters regen health so fast. Clerics can buff and heal only adjacent units not in combat and that consitutes a move for that team.   <BR> <BR>The winner is of course, the team that kills the opposing team&#39;s king. Nay sure what the prizes would by, maybe a small cash prize would go everyone that particpated with a slighty larger cash prize going to the winning team and possibly one good item to random off among the winners.  <BR> <BR>Another possible event that also takes some coordination is short dungeon raids. Get a few druid or wizard volunteers and grab a bunch of dwarves and head off to an appropriate level dungeon for a lighting strike with high level clerics/paladins supporting the group&#40;s&#41; with heals, buffs, resses, etc.  <BR> <BR>Thats all i can think of at the moment. Will add more idears later. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
